Double-action trigger. Operates on the classic Browning short-recoil principle.
Slide mounted decocking & saftey lever.
Metal-frame constructed from hard-coated investment cast A356T6 aluminum alloy.
Barrel fabricated from heat-treated 400-series stainless steel.
Other small parts (including hammer and trigger) made of stainless steel for longevity and holding up under harsh, moist conditions. Barrel: 4.5 inches long.
Oversize trigger guard to permit safe function with a gloved hand. Front of the trigger guard bow is recurved to accommodate the support-hand forefinger in a two-hand hold.
The rear sight is dovetail drift-adjustable for windage; front and rear sights have white-dot inserts for high visibility.
Unlike many competitors, Ruger completely re-engineered the 45 caliber gun (it is NOT a worked over 9mm). For example, the slide is 0.100 inches thicker than the Ruger 9mm to accommodate the larger 45 round,
In addition to the increased thickness of the P90 slide, there are several other external differences between it and previous P-Series pistols. Trigger mechanism was completely redesigned from the 9mm -- the result is a double-action trigger pull that is distinctly smoother and more even.  The release on the P90 is reversible; you decide which side you want it on and then leave it there until you change your mind.   
Ruger also upgraded the 45 floorplate over the 9mm model. It has an embossed Ruger eagle contoured to blend into the angles of the butt of the grip frame.  The floorplate is also thicker, allowing for a more positive seating when thrust home in a rapid under-pressure reload. 
A real pleasure to shoot and certainly as concealable as the ever popular Model 1911. It feels good in the hand and shoots well.
Ruger targeted this to be a “PDW”—Personal Defense Weapon— the standard to which they are engineered. According to military and law-enforcement procurement specifications, that amounts to 4.5-inch overall accuracy at 25 yards. The P90 passes with flying colors.  It’s a fine firearm and combines Ruger’s well-proven reliability, strength, and dependable performance with the greatest and most classic of all pistol cartridges.
